The paper is about the Coq system, which is a proof assistant for formal verification of mathematical proofs and software programs. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). Additionally, the paper discusses defining logical concepts and functions, which falls under cs.PL (Programming Languages) and cs.SE (Software Engineering). The paper also mentions reasoning about concepts, which is related to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory).
